Given the complexity and diversity of house sales, traditional machine learning algorithms may not always capture all the intricacies that affect house prices. In this case, we can use a rule-based system that leverages expert knowledge and domain-specific heuristics to predict house prices.

One approach could involve creating a set of rules that assign weights to different features of the house. For example, the number of bedrooms, condition of the house, and the quality of the kitchen, among other factors, could be weighted and summed to provide a predicted sales price.

Here's how this might look when implemented in the predictHousePrice function:

