One novel way to predict house prices is to use a decision tree model. A decision tree can capture non-linear relationships between the input features and the output (in this case, the house price) and can handle categorical and numerical data effectively.

The decision tree can be trained on historical house price data to learn how different combinations of house characteristics affect the price. The model can then be used to predict the price of a new house based on its features.

